Name: Aluminum Dish
Description: Sample handled or stored in an aluminum dish

Name: Aluminum Foil Wrap
Description: Sample secured within wrapper of aluminum foil

Name: BOD Bottle
Description: Sample bottle designed for use in measuring Biological Oxygen Demand (BOD)

Name: Carboy Container
Description: Sample container designed for large samples

Name: Glass Tube
Description: Sample container designed for blood collection

Name: Glass Vial w/ Septa
Description: Sample container designed for collection of Volatile Organic Compounds (VOCs)

Name: HDPE Bottle
Description: Sample bottle made of High Density Poly Ethylene (HDPE)

Name: HDPE Vial
Description: Sample vial made of High Density Poly Ethylene (HDPE)

Name: PETG Bottle
Description: Sample bottle made of Polyethylene terephthalate glycol (PETG); Used in Sampling Harmful Algal Blooms-Microcystins can adhere to other types of plastic

Name: Plastic Dilution Bottle
Description: Container designed for auto-dilution of sample

Name: Plastic Syringe
Description: A device used to transfer liquids into or out of a sampling area. It is made up of a hollow needle, which is attached to a tube and a plunger.

Name: Polystyrene Petri Dish
Description: Sample placed directly into a Petri Dish

Name: SPMD
Description: Semipermeable membrane device; also called "fatbag". It's a device that mimics parts of aquatic animals that cause bioconcentration.  SPMDs are used to assess contamination in water and air
